This paper deals with automated formal verification of microarchitectural memory consistency, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of abstraction to enable scalable verification, which is a common technique in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also presents case studies on different memory models, which could fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
